<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#D0BC90">Originally posted by Niku'a on 10-29-2002 07:08 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Just finished the game, restarting with a mage. Anyway here are my final stats just before killing the final boss.

Level 50 Warrior, could have been 51 if I had chosen the level up instead of strength at the wishing well.

Experience: 43 004 745
Next Level: 44 200 000
Vit: 1616, Magic: 524, STR: 160, AGI: 125, INT: 68, CON: 187, OFF & DEF: 104, DAM: 142-197 (using Blade of Chaos, lvl 3 frost and lvl 5 lightning and fire damage; plus lvl 5 poison and spiritual damage and damage increased), Armor: 228, Resistances: Lightning: 100, Fire: 100, Poison: 95, Spirit: 105, Reputation: 33, Weight: 4800 (encumbered at 3600), Gold: over 50000, and I was stupid enough to leave around 75000 at my house in Verdistis when entering the Wastelands.

Now for the skills I put points in. 
Q: Quest related, B: Bought, F: Found, A: Added myself, I: Item Boost, The number behind stands for how many I put in, bought etc.

Deadly Discs: B1, Polymorph: F1, Hell Spikes: F1, Telekinesis: A1, Wizard's Sight: F1, Bless: Q1, Restoration: Q3-F2, Withering Curse: F1, Fade From Sight: F1, Spellshield: F1, Freeze: A1, Meteorstrike: F1, Summon Skeleton: F1-I1, Banish: Q1, Transfer Powers: I1, Lockpick: A3-Q2, Pickpocket: A2-I1, Evade Trap: A1, Identify: A3-Q1, Alchemy: A3-Q1, Trader's Tongue: Q2, Wisdom: A5, Magic Barrier: A5, Aura of Command: Q1, Survivors Instinct: A5, Sword Expertise: A5, Axe Expertise: A1, Augment Damage: A4-Q1, Repair: A3, Augment Defense: A5, Poison Damage: A5, Enchant Weapon: A5, Boomerang: Q1, Spiritual Damage: A5, Spirit Form: Q1, Heaven's Blessing: A2.

A whole lot of them. As I first started out I was thinking of going with axes, but as you need high STR and AGI for that, I kept it with swords. That explains the 1 point in Axe Expertise. 
I was fortunate to get all 5 Restoration points just by the game, but I didn't really need it that much. Only in the first part of the game i used it, and as soon as Survivors Instinct was at 4 and even more at 5, I only used a health potion once.
For Identify I found very early on in the game a ring with Identify +1, so it wasn't needed to put an extra point in that one. Just by wearing it in occasion I could identify lvl 5 objects.
When I reached high levels, around 40, I didn't know where to put points in. So I put 2 more in Repair and even 2 in Heaven's Blessing. I was lvl 50 then and I just put them there to get rid of them.

Skills I can recommend: Wisdom, Survivor's Instinct, Lockpicking, Identify, your weapon of choice, Augment Damage and Defense, Poison and Spiritual Damage and Enchant. As a warrior I hardly used a spell except for Restoration in the beginning, and Freeze. But as soon as I had the Blade of Chaos this became useless.


------------------
That is not dead which can eternal lie, 
And with strange eons even death may die.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
